 Leckner Ford Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram Grand Opening 
         










    










 













 











 



















Leckner Ford Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram Grand Opening
        																																						
              











 News provided by
Leckner Auto Group  
Apr 28, 2016, 09:05 ET









 Share this article




























































KING GEORGE, Va., April 28, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- Please join us May 14th 10 am -3 pm for the Leckner Ford and Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram Grand Opening.
This event is open to the public, free food, entertainment and more.  The event will feature Country Station 93.3 WFLS - live broadcast, NASCAR sensation David Polenz #33, Tommy Wood – country singer, Ann's Wings and Thing – BBQ, Moon-bounce, pony-rides and activities with prizes.








Leckner FordLeckner Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram16057 James Madison PkwyKing George, VA 22485540-709-1280
Honored Guest:The Honorable Ruby Brabo At-Large Supervisor, King George County, Virginia.Kathleen Harrigan – Friends of the Rappahannock David Jones – Friends of the Dahlgren RR trailVicky Tate – King George Animal Shelter
LecknerA family owned automotive group, dedicated to saving people up to $100 per month on their monthly car payment.  We support the communities in which we serve through generous donations, corporate sponsorship of community organizations and participation of employees in community events. Our goal is to enrich the employees and the community we serve with superior products, value pricing and creating a great place to work. www.leckner.com
Economic impact:Leckner purchased the Ford and Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram franchise within the last 4 months. Leckner has more than doubled the number of employees from 23 to 54 at two dealerships.  We have increase sales from 35 units to 160 per month.  Leckner has brought an economic benefit to King George County, Virginia by increasing the number of high-paying skilled jobs.  Further, we have increased the total amount of retail sales tax paid and provided additional spending in the community we serve.
Community Involvement:Leckner Ford served over 250 Thanksgiving meal to low-income family in King George county with our partnership with the King George School System. We support the Friends of the Rappahannock, the local YMCA and the Guadeloupe Free Clinic in Colonial Beach.
Our Event Partners:WLFS Country radio – 93.3. Will be on-hand with a live remote broadcast.
David Polenz Racing NASCAR #33. David will be making an appearance with his #33 Machine. Kids and even adults are welcome to come sit in the racecar.
Tommy Wood – Country Singer – Ruckersville, Virginia. Tommy will be performing live.
For additional information please contact Kevin Scrimgeour, Director of Marketing, KScrimgeour@lecknerAuto.com or 301-346-1962.
Event page: www.lecknerford.com/grand-opening.htm
To view the original version on PR Newswire, visit:http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/leckner-ford-chrysler-dodge-jeep-ram-grand-opening-300258807.html
SOURCE  Leckner Auto Group
 Related Links

http://www.lecknerford.com/grand-opening.htm



 













